Package: wildcatdown
Title: An R Markdown thesis template for the Kansas State University
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Chester", "Ismay", email = "chester.ismay@gmail.com", role = c("cre", "aut")),
    person("Nick", "Solomon", email = "nick@nicksolomon.me", role = "aut"),
    person("Ben", "Marwick", email = "benmarwick@gmail.com", role = "aut"),
    person("Emrah", "Er", email = "eer@eremrah.com", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Using the bookdown package and LaTeX and Word thesis templates from
    KSU, this package aims to encourage reproducible research using
    simple Markdown syntax while embedding all of the R code to produce plots
    and analyses as well. Based on Chester Ismay's thesisdown and Ben Marwick's huskydown.
Maintainer: Emrah Er <eer@eremrah.com>
Depends:
    R (>= 3.4.4)
Imports:
    bookdown,
    rmarkdown,
    knitr,
    git2r,
    tinytex,
    devtools,
    dplyr,
    ggplot2
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
SystemRequirements: pandoc (>= 1.18) - http://pandoc.org
Suggests: 
    testthat
